WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:00.429 --> 00:00:05.470
From shackled skulls to books that are literally
wrapped in human skin, there have been things

00:00:05.470 --> 00:00:08.690
found by archaeologists that will chill you
to the bone!

00:00:08.690 --> 00:00:12.380
Here are 12 of the most terrifying archaeological
discoveries ever.

00:00:19.300 --> 00:00:20.680
12.

00:00:20.680 --> 00:00:25.040
Headless Gladiators
Let's start off with a combat one.

00:00:25.040 --> 00:00:28.710
In York, England, a large set of skeletal
remains were found buried.

00:00:28.710 --> 00:00:33.480
This isn't too bad on their own, however,
when the remains were fully uncovered, they

00:00:33.480 --> 00:00:37.850
found that every single person that was buried
there was missing their head.

00:00:37.850 --> 00:00:43.470
What's more, they were buried with their heads
alongside them, which made it even more odd,

00:00:43.470 --> 00:00:44.830
and scary.

00:00:44.830 --> 00:00:48.690
After some research and study, scientists
dated the bodies back to around the second

00:00:48.690 --> 00:00:54.399
and fourth centuries, A.D. which lead to speculation
that these might have been gladiators.

00:00:54.399 --> 00:00:58.250
This theory was supported when when the bones
of the victims were shown to have clear battle

00:00:58.250 --> 00:00:59.250
wounds.

00:00:59.250 --> 00:01:02.610
Other people believe that they could have
been soldiers, but it's impossible to tell

00:01:02.610 --> 00:01:03.980
either way.

00:01:03.980 --> 00:01:08.369
No matter what they did for a living, this
raises a very disturbing question.

00:01:08.369 --> 00:01:13.040
Regardless of whether they were soldiers or
gladiators, why were they decapitated then

00:01:13.040 --> 00:01:14.180
buried with their heads?

00:01:14.180 --> 00:01:18.810
It's clear that they weren't thrown in, the
heads I mean, they were placed in specific

00:01:18.810 --> 00:01:21.120
spots from body to body.

00:01:21.120 --> 00:01:25.750
Which says that they were buried there with
care and detail, but to what end?

00:01:25.750 --> 00:01:29.500
The archaeologists are just as confused as
we are.

00:01:29.500 --> 00:01:30.700
11.

00:01:30.700 --> 00:01:34.050
Screaming Mummies
Sticking with the past in a big way, let's

00:01:34.050 --> 00:01:35.600
talk about mummies.

00:01:35.600 --> 00:01:40.040
They're a well-documented part of archaeology,
and some of the biggest discoveries in history

00:01:40.040 --> 00:01:44.820
have been finding mummies and their crypts
and tombs and discovering who they were and

00:01:44.820 --> 00:01:45.820
what they did.

00:01:45.820 --> 00:01:50.710
The process to examine these former rulers,
like Tutankhamun is extensive, as doing it

00:01:50.710 --> 00:01:56.619
the wrong way will cause the body to disintegrate...The
mummy's, not the archaeologist although there

00:01:56.619 --> 00:01:59.540
are some curses around that they should watch
out for!

00:01:59.540 --> 00:02:04.990
However, a trend was discovered back in 1886
in regards to improper mummification that

00:02:04.990 --> 00:02:08.259
surely scared the crap out of the archaeologist
at the time.

00:02:08.259 --> 00:02:10.969
For he discovered...a screaming mummy.

00:02:10.969 --> 00:02:15.269
Of course it wasn’t alive and screaming,
but rather, the pose and posture of the mummy

00:02:15.269 --> 00:02:17.099
made it look like it was screaming.

00:02:17.099 --> 00:02:20.970
Can you imagine brushing the dirt off of its
face and its mouth close up while it’s frozen

00:02:20.970 --> 00:02:22.439
in a scream?

00:02:22.439 --> 00:02:26.829
This naturally lead to much speculation as
to how this mummy ended up this way!

00:02:26.829 --> 00:02:27.999
Was he buried alive?

00:02:27.999 --> 00:02:28.999
In pain?

00:02:28.999 --> 00:02:32.029
Well, apparently, it's all about following
procedure.

00:02:32.029 --> 00:02:35.749
When we die, our body gets rigid, the process
called Rigor Mortis.

00:02:35.749 --> 00:02:40.189
However, after a while our body relaxes, and
allows itself to rest.

00:02:40.189 --> 00:02:45.309
This is no different with mummies, and because
of that, if the jaw isn't fastened shut, (which

00:02:45.309 --> 00:02:49.950
is a practice in proper mummification), it
will go slack, and fall open.

00:02:49.950 --> 00:02:55.549
And without skin or muscles to give context,
it looks like a screaming mummy.

00:02:55.549 --> 00:02:59.279
Despite being explained by science, it would
still be creepy as heck if you turned around

00:02:59.279 --> 00:03:01.549
and saw one staring at you!!

00:03:01.549 --> 00:03:06.339
And now for number 10, but first if you are
a returning subscriber, welcome back!!!

00:03:06.339 --> 00:03:07.589
Glad to see you again!!

00:03:07.589 --> 00:03:09.250
Can any of you identify this noise??

00:03:09.250 --> 00:03:18.939
